/PGMOTZEY SHABBAT/XX524/XX/PR
With the permission of this company:/PR
Blessed are you, /SCT/XXHE /XXB/XXOUNDLESS /XXO/XXNE/XX, our God, the sovereign
of all worlds, who created the fruit of the vine./PR
/ITIt is the custom in some families for everyone to take a sip of the wine here. Others wait
until after the final /MDberah/±ah/XX / blessing./PR
/PR
Blessed are you, /SCR/XXEVIVER/XX our God, the sovereign of all worlds,
who creates various spices./PR
/ITAfter the blessing is said, the leader smells the spices and passes them on./PR
/PR
Blessed are you, /SCT/XXHE /XXR/XXADIANCE/XX, our God, the sovereign of all
worlds, who creates the light of fire./PR
/ITAfter reciting the blessing over fire, participants hold their hands before the candle flame so
that their fingers look radiant in its light and then cast shadows on their palms. Then the
following blessing is said./PR
/PR
Blessed are you, /SCT/XXHE /XXM/XXANY-/XXN/XXAMED/XX, our God, the sovereign of
all worlds, who separates between holy and ordinary, light and
dark, the seventh day and the six days of work. Blessed are you,
/SCT/XXHE /XXI/XXNVISIBLE/XX who separates the holy from the ordinary./PR
/ITThe candle is now extinguished. Some families do this by immersing it in wine from the
cup. Lights are turned on, and we continue in lively song./PR
/PR
/SCC/XXOMMENTARY/XX. While lighting candles marks both the beginning and the
end of Shabbat, the /ITHavdalah/XX candle has a meaning different from that of
the /ITErev Shabbat/XX candles. Lighting this new fire signals commencement of
the work week because fire is so often an instrument of labor. Every
/ITberah/±ah/XX / blessing must correlate to an event or action so that it is not in
vain. We "use" the candlelight here to cast a shadow on our palms by
lifting our curled fingers toward the light./PR
/PR
A time of transitions, /ITHavdalah/XX lends itself to comment about life cycle
transitions as well. It is a wonderful place to insert parentsÚ hopes for a
bar / bat mitzvah at the transition from childhood to adolescence. /ITBrit/XX cer-
emonies for new-born girls can easily be created around /ITHavdalah/XX. Wed-
dings, new jobs, beginning of school and graduation are some of the occa-
sions when people might want to add personal words to /ITHavdalah/XX./PR
/SC/XXD.A.T./XX/PR
